{{!
    @template core/col_tabs

    Moodle tabs template.

    The purpose of this template is to render a list of tabs
    with content.

    Classes required for JS:
    * active on the tab li to indicate it is the active tab.
    * tab-pane to indicate element is a tab panel.

    Data attributes required for JS:
    * href required on anchor tag in tab list. Must match id of tab panel.
    * data-toggle="tab" required on an anchor element within the tab list.
    * role="tabpanel" required on each panel element.

    Context variables required for this template:
    * tabs A list of objects to represent. See below:
    ** active (optional) bool Should this tab be active by default.
    ** id Identifier to uniquely identify this tab within the list.
    ** name Display name for the tab
    ** content Content to display in the tab panel for this tab.

    Example context (json):
    {
        "tabs": [
            {"id":"tab1","name":"Tab 1","content":"This is tab 1 content <a href='#'>test</a>"},
            {"id":"tab2","name":"Tab 2","content":"This is tab 2 content <a href='#'>test</a>"},
            {"id":"tab3","name":"Tab 3","content":"This is tab 3 content <a href='#'>test</a>"}
        ]
    }
}}
{{< core/tabs }}
    {{$ tabheader }}
        <div role="tablist" class="row-fluid">
            {{# tabs }}
                <div class="span4">
                    <a data-target="#{{ uniqid }}-{{ id }}"
                        role="tab">

                        {{ name }}
                    </a>
                </div>
            {{/ tabs }}
        </div>
    {{/ tabheader }}
{{/ core/tabs }}
